rce":"recI1mfPyvrG11DC9","target":"rechkAyIwugqcLaaY","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recI1mfPyvrG11DC9","target":"recvAB7vkczUEFH8Z","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recI1mfPyvrG11DC9","target":"recmKQbYJdJMGjw23","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recI1mfPyvrG11DC9","target":"recMTSIklCghjlACt","label":"event"},{"source":"recI1mfPyvrG11DC9","target":"recY3vd5gVnwqoRV1","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recl67r4YUZ7vGJE6","ref":"Mark.5.1","text":"And they came over unto the other side of the sea, into the country of the Gadarenes.","year":31},{"id":"reckVSLBKscibaRc8","ref":"Mark.5.2","text":"And when he was come out of the ship, immediately there met him out of the tombs a man with an unclean spirit,","year":31},{"id":"recPvmEzWfRN76VNB","ref":"Mark.5.3","text":"Who had his dwelling among the tombs; and no man could bind him, no, not with chains:","year":31},{"id":"recIzeXUmt2xn0IER","ref":"Mark.5.4","text":"Because that he had been often bound with fetters and chains, and the chains had been plucked asunder by him, and the fetters broken in pieces: neither could any man tame him.","year":31},{"id":"recAQ89pIvErDV8zs","ref":"Mark.5.5","text":"And always, night and day, he was in the mountains, and in the tombs, crying, and cutting himself with stones.","year":31},{"id":"recdzRqMDpfynPSXC","ref":"Mark.5.6","text":"But when he saw Jesus afar off, he ran and worshipped him,","year":31},{"id":"rec5SaRipCTU36NZR","ref":"Mark.5.7","text":"And cried with a loud voice, and said, What have I to do with thee, Jesus, thou Son of the most high God? I adjure thee by God, that thou torment me not.","year":31},{"id":"recUHp7cKo97mWD18","ref":"Mark.5.8","text":"For he said unto him, Come out of the man, thou unclean spirit.","year":31}]}
